data.text:
On the the sudsiduary companies we look after from the UK is having problems with the speed of their SDSL line in the Netherlands.

I don’t know any specific ISPs that are Netherlands based (apart from KPN - the current provider). I’ve had a quick scoot around, but cannot many apart from Multikabel and Casema.

Do any one know of any other ? and what do you think of them ?

Thanks in advance,

Nik

A few isp’s

Cabel → ziggo.nl and ziggozakelijk.nl (dutch language)

XS4all.nl (kpn daughter) → ADSL SDSL- use this one for my customers and my own business.

online.nl → adsl -use this one for my home adsl.

tele2.nl →

all these have a good quality
